  <description><![CDATA[<p>The beautiful Therasia Resort Sea &amp; Spa offers total relaxation in a truly luxurious setting. The infinity pools and terraces planted have breath-taking views over the entire <a data-udi="umb://document/c2a0cfb0af8146d18a45e08bc4c22d42" href="/{localLink:umb://document/c2a0cfb0af8146d18a45e08bc4c22d42}" title="Aeolian Islands">Aeolian</a> archipelago, all the way to lively Stromboli. Created with typical local materials such as lava rock, <a data-udi="umb://document/b037a20c14a3421ba33b32859c9e3344" href="/{localLink:umb://document/b037a20c14a3421ba33b32859c9e3344}" title="Sicily">Sicilian</a> terracotta and cedar wood there is a distinct Mediterranean feel in the guest rooms.</p>
<p>There are three excellent restaurants including L'Arcipelago that has a panoramic sea view terrace where you can dine under the stars, Il Cappero, a Michelin Star restaurant and I Grusoni that serves light lunches by the pool and typical Sicilian cuisine. Head for the Lounge Bar to enjoy a few cocktails or a nightcap whilst taking in the wonderful views and live music.</p>
<p>Transfer time: approx. 1 hour 45 mins by private car to Milazzo Port from Catania Airport; approx. 1 hour 40 by hydrofoil/ferry from Milazzo Port &amp; approx 10 mins by hotel shuttle from Vulcano Port.</p>
<p>* Please note that the ferry ticket to the island is payable locally for approx. €20 per person one way.</p>]]></description>
